Consultation Agreement
Date: dd/mm/yyyy
Parties:
This Joint Venture Agreement is made between QMS Resourcing Services Ltd (registered number:
03836478) of 141 Cutenhoe Road, Luton, Bedfordshire, United Kingdom (QMSrs)
and
Consultant Name Address .
Term
This Agreement shall commence on the date it is signed by both Parties (the "Commencement Date") and
shall continue unless terminated in accordance with the terms herein.
Background
QMSrs has been seeking a reliable and professional consultant, with local market knowledge and contacts
of the Country region, to promote and sell its products and services.
Consultant Name is an experienced and knowledgeable independent consultant and will take up
QMSrs activity as an independent consultant.
Purpose
QMSrs and Consultant Namewish to enter into a Consultation Partnership to address Quality
Management Solutions market within Country. Consultant Name will operate as an independent
consultant and shall be rewarded with commission payments as detailed below.
QMSrs will provide all the technical knowledge, consultation services, products and marketing collateral
(brochures, presentations, demos etc.).
Consultant Name will provide all the marketing and sales activity.
Scope of Agreement
Consultant Name will act as a Consultant for QMSrs within Country on a non-exclusive basis and
will provide the following services:
1. Assist QMSrs to market its products and services in the Country territory for all industries
2. Introduce QMSrs to new customers (those unknown to QMSrs at the time of introduction)
3. Act as a Consultant on behalf of QMSrs at customers introduced by Consultant Name
4. Act as a Consultant for direct customers of QMSrs at the request of QMSrs
Contribution from Each Party:
1. QMSrs will provide the following services and products:
Make available all of QMSrs products and services for Consultant Name to promote and sell to
any customer within Country

Provide full training for Consultant Name to ensure a good level of understanding of the
services and products
Support Consultant Name with pre-sales and after-sales service
Provide appropriate resources where necessary to facilitate the Sales process
Supply Consultant Name with existing contacts generated by QMSrs in Country
QMSrs shall supply details of existing references
QMSrs will honour confidentiality with Consultant Name
2. Consultant Name will provide the following services:
Market and sell all QMSrs products and services without exception
Ensure that QMSrs activity is the main focus, however as an independent consultant, Consultant
Name is free accept tasks from other sources.
Other Consultant Name activities must not conflict with QMSrs
Consultant Name will generate an agreed marketing strategy and detailed sales forecast
Consultant Name will be responsible for on-going marketing to achieve agreed objectives
Consultant Name will provide full visibility of the status of all activities, financial, technical and
operational
Commission Payment
As a reward for the tasks performed and sales deals closed by Consultant Name; QMSrs will pay a
commission as follows:
To facilitate an immediate and quick start to the Partnership; QMSrs will provide to Consultant
Name a full list of all existing customers with which the company has existing or on-going
dialogue with a view to closing a sale. For all these customers QMSrs will pay a commission of
10% of the sale price to Consultant Name.
For all other customers which Consultant Name independently brings to QMSrs; the company
will pay a commission of 15% of sales price to Consultant Name
QMSrs will pay a finders fee of 2% of the sales price where Consultant Name introduces a
customer to the company but does not perform any further activity with that customer.
Notes:
1. The commission fee will only be paid to Consultant Name after the customer has paid QMSrs
2. For the first five (5) customers QMSrs will pay the commission fee in full (either 10% or 15%
depending on the source of customer as explained above) as soon as the customers has made the
first agreed payment to QMSrs
3. After the first five (5) customers QMSrs will pay commission fees on back-to-back basis with
customer payments to QMSrs
4. The Sales Price means the price stated on the final invoice submitted to customer
5. Finders Fee means where Consultant Name has only introduced the customer to QMSrs and has
taken no further active part in winning that customer
6. Commission Fee means where Consultant Name has actively been involved in the marketing,
selling, training and consultation of that customer
7. The Commission fee is only valid for customers introduced by Consultant Name to QMSrs
8. This agreement or commission does not apply to direct customers of QMSrs
Non-Competence
During lifetime of this Agreement (as defined below) and for 12 months after the conclusion of this
Agreement, Consultant Name shall not engage in any activity in direct competition with QMSrs,

Termination of Agreement
1. Termination by Agreement or on Notice
Each party may terminate this Agreement at any time by mutual consent. This Agreement may be
terminated by either party at any time prior to the end of the agreement by giving sixty (60) days written
notice of termination. Such notice may be given at any time for any reason, with or without cause.
In addition, the Parties shall provide to each other a final report on the status of their work for the project
even though the work is not completed.
2. Termination on Default
In the event of a default the Parties shall have no further obligation to contribute to the cost of the project
and may require that the defaulting party transfer clear title and an unrestricted right to use the Intellectual
Property Rights in foreground and background information to the other party.
Mediation and Arbitration
In the event of any dispute between the Parties arising out of the construction, meaning or effect of any clause
or matter contained in this Agreement or of the rights and liabilities of the Parties, the Parties shall endeavour to
settle the matter through bona fide negotiations.
Failing an amicable settlement to any such dispute, each party may request, by sending a written notice to the
other party, that the dispute shall be referred to binding arbitration. This arbitration shall be subject to the
following rules:
The Parties shall jointly appoint a single arbitrator. If the Parties cannot agree on the choice of an
Arbitrator, each Party shall appoint an arbitrator, and both arbitrators shall jointly appoint a third
arbitrator.
Each Party shall pay its own costs and shall bear an equal share of all other arbitration costs as well as
the fees of the arbitrator.
The Parties may jointly determine, by written agreement, the procedure to be followed by the
arbitrator in conducting the proceedings, or may request the arbitrator to do so.
The hearing shall take place in the United Kingdom.
The arbitrator shall issue a written award within thirty days following the completion of the hearing.
This award cannot include punitive damages or an award for costs.
Subject to the provisions of the Commercial Arbitration Code, the award shall be final and binding on
the Parties.
Events Constituting Default
The following events constitute default:
a Party becomes bankrupt or insolvent or goes into receivership
an order is made or resolution passed winding down or dissolving a Party
a Party ceases to carry on business
a Party submits false or misleading information to the other Party or makes a false representation or
a Party fails to proceed diligently with the Project
Non-Solicitation.

During the life of this Agreement and for a period of one (1) year thereafter, Consultant Name will
directly or indirectly recruit, solicit or hire any employee of QMSrs, or induce or attempt to induce any
employee of QMSrs to terminate his/her employment with, or otherwise cease his/her relationship with
QMSrs.
Confidential Information
At all times, both during the term of this Agreement and after its termination, both Parties will keep in
confidence and trust, and will not use or disclose, any Proprietary Information without the prior written
consent of an officer of the QMSrs, except as may be necessary in the ordinary course of performing the
services under this Agreement.
Assignment or Amendment
This Agreement may be amended or varied by instrument in writing duly executed by both Parties. No
party shall assign any or all of its interest or obligations in this Agreement unless the prior written consent
of the other Parties to this Agreement is obtained. This Agreement shall endure to the benefit of and be
binding on the Parties, their successors, representatives and permitted assigns.
Governing Law
This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the United Kingdom
(according to English Law).
Language of choice
This Agreement has been drafted in English at the express wish of the Parties
Entire Agreement
This Agreement constitutes this entire agreement between the Parties and supersedes all prior agreements
and understandings, whether written or oral, relating to the subject matter of this Agreement.
